            <p class="is-small">Lapis Lazuli, otherwise known as just Lapis, is an internal project name.</p>
            <p>
                Lapis Lazuli is a self-hostable, secure, E2E encrypted community-based communication platform, melding the ideas behind <a href="https://discord.com" is-external="true">Discord</a> and <a href="https://matrix.org" is-external="true">Matrix</a>. 
                This does not strive to be a replacement for either platform, but users from both communities may like to leverage a common set of features.
            </p>
            <p>Lapis Lazuli is currently under development. The following features are planned:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Centralized chat service,</li>
                <li>Compliance with some Matrix standards (will not be fully compatible),</li>
                <li>Open client API to connect user-provided clients,</li>
                <li>Open bot API to connect automated services,</li>
                <li>E2E encrypted private messaging and groups chats</li>
                <li>Secure community spaces with integrated text, voice, and content channels (markdown pages, calendar system, and more),</li>
                <li>Granular role-based permissions system,</li>
                <li>Zero trackers, zero ads, and only anonymous analytics (number of users in community, generalized activity levels)</li>
            </ul>
